thread.title: After coming close year before, ’72 Dolphins finished the job

author: Michael Lerseth
title: After coming close year before, ’72 Dolphins finished the job
text:
Photo: Anonymous Garo Yepremian provided the most memorable play in Super Bowl VII when his fumble went to Washington’s Mike Bass, who ran for a TD. But Miami got the last laugh with a 14-7 victory. Garo Yepremian provided the most memorable play in Super Bowl VII...
Neither offense did much. The winning quarterback threw for fewer than 90 yards. And the game’s most memorable play featured the winning team’s kicker comically mishandling a blocked field-goal try that led to the losing team’s only score.
